00:18:09.380 --> 00:18:10.270
much out of it.

00:18:10.270 --> 00:18:12.690
DAN GALPIN: With strace,
unfortunately, this is all

00:18:12.690 --> 00:18:13.150
deck stuff.

00:18:13.150 --> 00:18:14.540
So strace would just
let me know it was

00:18:14.540 --> 00:18:16.220
trying to load a file.

00:18:16.220 --> 00:18:17.330
strace is really cool, though.

00:18:17.330 --> 00:18:18.930
If you're trying to debug native
stuff, it's actually

00:18:18.930 --> 00:18:23.080
really, really useful to know
which call your app made that

